{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_1c07905a8f0d4b61848587d9","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t[<img src=\"https://beeware.org/project/briefcase/briefcase.png\" width=\"72\" alt=\"logo\" />](https://beeware.org/briefcase)\n2\t\n3\t# Briefcase\n4\t\n5\t[![Python Versions](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/briefcase.svg)](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/briefcase)\n6\t[![PyPI Version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/briefcase.svg)](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/briefcase)\n7\t[![Maturity](https://img.shields.io/pypi/status/briefcase.svg)](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/briefcase)\n8\t[![BSD License](https://img.shields.io/pypi/l/briefcase.svg)](https://github.com/beeware/briefcase/blob/main/LICENSE)\n9\t[![Build Status](https://github.com/beeware/briefcase/workflows/CI/badge.svg?branch=main)](https://github.com/beeware/briefcase/actions)\n10\t[![Discord server](https://img.shields.io/discord/836455665257021440?label=Discord%20Chat&logo=discord&style=plastic)](https://beeware.org/bee/chat/)\n11\t\n12\tBriefcase is a tool for converting a Python project into a standalone native application. You can package projects for:\n13\t\n14\t- Mac\n15\t- Windows\n16\t- Linux\n17\t- iPhone/iPad\n18\t- Android\n19\t- Web\n20\t\n21\tSupport for AppleTV, watchOS, and wearOS deployments is planned.\n22\t\n23\t## Getting started\n24\t\n25\tTo install Briefcase, run:\n26\t\n27\t    $ python -m pip install briefcase\n28\t\n29\tIf you would like a full introduction to using Briefcase, try the [BeeWare tutorial](https://tutorial.beeware.org). This tutorial walks you through the process of creating and packaging a new application with Briefcase.\n30\t\n31\t## Financial support\n32\t\n33\tThe BeeWare project would not be possible without the generous support of our financial members:\n34\t\n35\t[![Anaconda logo](https://beeware.org/images/anaconda-dark.png)](https://anaconda.com/)\n36\t\n37\tAnaconda Inc. - Advancing AI through open source.\n38\t\n39\tPlus individual contributions from [users like you](https://beeware.org/community/members/). If you find Briefcase, or other BeeWare tools useful, please consider becoming a financial member.\n40\t\n41\t## Documentation\n42\t\n43\tDocumentation for Briefcase can be found on [Read The Docs](https://briefcase.beeware.org).\n44\t\n45\t## Community\n46\t\n47\tBriefcase is part of the [BeeWare suite](https://beeware.org). You can talk to the community through:\n48\t\n49\t- [@beeware@fosstodon.org on Mastodon](https://fosstodon.org/@beeware)\n50\t- [Discord](https://beeware.org/bee/chat/)\n51\t- The Briefcase [GitHub Discussions forum](https://github.com/beeware/briefcase/discussions)\n52\t\n53\tWe foster a welcoming and respectful community as described in our [BeeWare Community Code of Conduct](https://beeware.org/community/behavior/).\n54\t\n55\t## Contributing\n56\t\n57\tIf you experience problems with Briefcase, [log them on GitHub](https://github.com/beeware/briefcase/issues).\n58\t\n59\tIf you'd like to contribute to Briefcase development, our [contribution guide](https://briefcase.beeware.org/en/latest/how-to/contribute) details how to set up a development environment, and other requirements we have as part of our contribution process.\n60\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ea01d3a9-8bbc-42c9-956e-bd48a919071a","uuid":"45ff1c7e-a844-4ee0-89ef-612fa112e113","timestamp":"2026-04-06T20:28:55.655Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.md","content":"[<img src=\"https://beeware.org/project/briefcase/briefcase.png\" width=\"72\" alt=\"logo\" />](https://beeware.org/briefcase)\n\n# Briefcase\n\n[![Python Versions](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/briefcase.svg)](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/briefcase)\n[![PyPI Version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/briefcase.svg)](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/briefcase)\n[![Maturity](https://img.shields.io/pypi/status/briefcase.svg)](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/briefcase)\n[![BSD License](https://img.shields.io/pypi/l/briefcase.svg)](https://github.com/beeware/briefcase/blob/main/LICENSE)\n[![Build Status](https://github.com/beeware/briefcase/workflows/CI/badge.svg?branch=main)](https://github.com/beeware/briefcase/actions)\n[![Discord server](https://img.shields.io/discord/836455665257021440?label=Discord%20Chat&logo=discord&style=plastic)](https://beeware.org/bee/chat/)\n\nBriefcase is a tool for converting a Python project into a standalone native application. You can package projects for:\n\n- Mac\n- Windows\n- Linux\n- iPhone/iPad\n- Android\n- Web\n\nSupport for AppleTV, watchOS, and wearOS deployments is planned.\n\n## Getting started\n\nTo install Briefcase, run:\n\n    $ python -m pip install briefcase\n\nIf you would like a full introduction to using Briefcase, try the [BeeWare tutorial](https://tutorial.beeware.org). This tutorial walks you through the process of creating and packaging a new application with Briefcase.\n\n## Financial support\n\nThe BeeWare project would not be possible without the generous support of our financial members:\n\n[![Anaconda logo](https://beeware.org/images/anaconda-dark.png)](https://anaconda.com/)\n\nAnaconda Inc. - Advancing AI through open source.\n\nPlus individual contributions from [users like you](https://beeware.org/community/members/). If you find Briefcase, or other BeeWare tools useful, please consider becoming a financial member.\n\n## Documentation\n\nDocumentation for Briefcase can be found on [Read The Docs](https://briefcase.beeware.org).\n\n## Community\n\nBriefcase is part of the [BeeWare suite](https://beeware.org). You can talk to the community through:\n\n- [@beeware@fosstodon.org on Mastodon](https://fosstodon.org/@beeware)\n- [Discord](https://beeware.org/bee/chat/)\n- The Briefcase [GitHub Discussions forum](https://github.com/beeware/briefcase/discussions)\n\nWe foster a welcoming and respectful community as described in our [BeeWare Community Code of Conduct](https://beeware.org/community/behavior/).\n\n## Contributing\n\nIf you experience problems with Briefcase, [log them on GitHub](https://github.com/beeware/briefcase/issues).\n\nIf you'd like to contribute to Briefcase development, our [contribution guide](https://briefcase.beeware.org/en/latest/how-to/contribute) details how to set up a development environment, and other requirements we have as part of our contribution process.\n","numLines":60,"startLine":1,"totalLines":60}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0b514c71b08c4229b9c6f89b","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t[build-system]\n2\trequires = [\n3\t    # keep versions in sync with automation/pyproject.toml\n4\t    \"setuptools==82.0.1\",\n5\t    \"setuptools_scm==10.0.5\",\n6\t]\n7\tbuild-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n8\t\n9\t[project]\n10\tdynamic = [\"version\"]\n11\tname = \"briefcase\"\n12\tdescription = \"Tools to support converting a Python project into a standalone native application.\"\n13\treadme = \"README.md\"\n14\trequires-python = \">= 3.10\"\n15\tlicense = \"BSD-3-Clause\"\n16\tlicense-files = [\n17\t    \"LICENSE\",\n18\t]\n19\tauthors = [\n20\t    {name=\"Russell Keith-Magee\", email=\"russell@keith-magee.com\"},\n21\t]\n22\tmaintainers = [\n23\t    {name=\"BeeWare Team\", email=\"team@beeware.org\"},\n24\t]\n25\tkeywords = [\n26\t    \"app\",\n27\t    \"packaging\",\n28\t    \"installer\",\n29\t    \"macOS\",\n30\t    \"iOS\",\n31\t    \"android\",\n32\t    \"mobile\",\n33\t    \"windows\",\n34\t    \"linux\",\n35\t    \"flatpak\",\n36\t    \"appimage\",\n37\t    \"deb\",\n38\t    \"rpm\",\n39\t    \"pkg\",\n40\t    \"tvOS\",\n41\t    \"watch\",\n42\t    \"watchOS\",\n43\t    \"wearos\",\n44\t    \"web\",\n45\t    \"pyscript\",\n46\t    \"pyodide\",\n47\t]\n48\tclassifiers = [\n49\t    \"Development Status :: 4 - Beta\",\n50\t    \"Intended Audience :: Developers\",\n51\t    \"Operating System :: OS Independent\",\n52\t    \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3\",\n53\t    \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10\",\n54\t    \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11\",\n55\t    \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12\",\n56\t    \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13\",\n57\t    \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.14\",\n58\t    \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3 :: Only\",\n59\t    \"Topic :: Software Development\",\n60\t    \"Topic :: Utilities\",\n61\t]\n62\tdependencies = [\n63\t    # Dependencies required at runtime are set as ranges to ensure maximum\n64\t    # compatibility with the end-user's development environment.\n65\t    #\n66\t    # Any dependency that is part of the \"core python toolchain\" (e.g. pip, wheel)\n67\t    # specify a minimum version, but no maximum, because we always want the most\n68\t    # recent version.\n69\t    \"packaging >= 24.2\",\n70\t    \"pip >= 24.3\",\n71\t    \"setuptools >= 60\",\n72\t    \"wheel >= 0.37\",\n73\t    \"build >= 0.10\",\n74\t    \"truststore >= 0.10.1\",\n75\t    #\n76\t    # For the remaining packages: We set the lower version limit to the lowest possible\n77\t    # version that satisfies our API needs. If the package uses semver, we set a limit\n78\t    # to prevent the next major version (which will potentially cause API breakages).\n79\t    # If the package uses calver, we don't pin the upper version, as the upper version\n80\t    # provides no basis for determining API stability.\n81\t    #\n82\t    \"cookiecutter >= 2.6.0, < 3.0\",\n83\t    # See psf/requests#7219. Requests 2.32.5 (a transitive dependency of cookiecutter)\n84\t    # has a runtime warning about the use of chardet 6+, which our test suite turns into\n85\t    # a full error. Requests has already increased the pin; the next requests release\n86\t    # should remove the need for this pin.\n87\t    \"chardet < 6.0\",\n88\t    # See binaryornot/binaryornot#642 and binaryornot/binaryornot#649. binaryornot is\n89\t    # transitive dependency of cookiecutter; v0.5.0 introduced #642, preventing correct\n90\t    # detection of PNG content (#642). v0.6.0 (released a few days later) fixes #642,\n91\t    # but introduced #649, and the presence of warnings causes catastrophic failures\n92\t    # when running under dev mode.\n93\t    \"binaryornot < 0.5.0\",\n94\t    \"dmgbuild >= 1.6.4, < 2.0; sys_platform == 'darwin'\",\n95\t    \"GitPython >= 3.1, < 4.0\",\n96\t    \"platformdirs >= 2.6, < 5.0\",\n97\t    \"psutil >= 5.9, < 8.0\",\n98\t    \"python-dateutil >= 2.9.0.post0\",  # transitive dependency (beeware/briefcase#1428)\n99\t    \"httpx >= 0.20, < 1.0\",\n100\t    \"rich >= 12.6, < 15.0\",\n101\t    \"tenacity >= 8.0, < 10.0\",\n102\t    \"tomli >= 2.0, < 3.0; python_version <= '3.10'\",\n103\t    \"tomli_w >= 1.0, < 2.0\",\n104\t]\n105\t\n106\t[dependency-groups]\n107\t# Extras used by developers *of* briefcase are pinned to specific versions to\n108\t# ensure environment consistency.\n109\tpre-commit = [\n110\t    \"pre-commit == 4.5.1\",\n111\t]\n112\t\n113\tsetuptools-scm = [\n114\t    \"setuptools_scm == 10.0.5\",\n115\t]\n116\t\n117\ttowncrier = [\n118\t    \"towncrier == 25.8.0\",\n119\t]\n120\t\n121\ttox-uv = [\n122\t    \"tox-uv == 1.34.0\",\n123\t]\n124\t\n125\tty = [\n126\t    \"ty == 0.0.29\",\n127\t]\n128\t\n129\tdev = [\n130\t    {include-group = \"pre-commit\"},\n131\t    {include-group = \"setuptools-scm\"},\n132\t    {include-group = \"tox-uv\"},\n133\t]\n134\t\n135\ttest = [\n136\t    \"coverage[toml] == 7.13.5\",\n137\t    \"coverage-conditional-plugin == 0.9.0\",\n138\t    \"httpx-retries == 0.4.6\",\n139\t    \"pytest == 9.0.2\",\n140\t    \"pytest-xdist == 3.8.0\",\n141\t    {include-group = \"setuptools-scm\"},\n142\t]\n143\t# Docs are always built on a specific Python version; see RTD and tox config files,\n144\t# and the docs contribution guide.\n145\tdocs = [\n146\t    \"beeware-docs-tools @ git+https://github.com/beeware/beeware-docs-tools\",\n147\t]\n148\t\n149\t[project.urls]\n150\tHomepage = \"https://beeware.org/briefcase\"\n151\tFunding = \"https://beeware.org/contributing/membership/\"\n152\tDocumentation = \"https://briefcase.readthedocs.io/en/latest/\"\n153\tTracker = \"https://github.com/beeware/briefcase/issues\"\n154\tSource = \"https://github.com/beeware/briefcase\"\n155\t\n156\t[project.scripts]\n157\tbriefcase = \"briefcase.__main__:main\"\n158\t\n159\t[project.entry-points.\"briefcase.bootstraps\"]\n160\tNone = \"briefcase.bootstraps.empty:EmptyBootstrap\"\n161\tToga = \"briefcase.bootstraps.toga:TogaGuiBootstrap\"\n162\tConsole = \"briefcase.bootstraps.console:ConsoleBootstrap\"\n163\tPySide6 = \"briefcase.bootstraps.pyside6:PySide6GuiBootstrap\"\n164\tPygame = \"briefcase.bootstraps.pygame:PygameGuiBootstrap\"\n165\t\n166\t[project.entry-points.\"briefcase.debuggers\"]\n167\tpdb = \"briefcase.debuggers.pdb:PdbDebugger\"\n168\tdebugpy = \"briefcase.debuggers.debugpy:DebugpyDebugger\"\n169\t\n170\t[project.entry-points.\"briefcase.platforms\"]\n171\tandroid = \"briefcase.platforms.android\"\n172\tiOS = \"briefcase.platforms.iOS\"\n173\tlinux = \"briefcase.platforms.linux\"\n174\tmacOS = \"briefcase.platforms.macOS\"\n175\t# tvOS = \"briefcase.platforms.tvOS\"\n176\t# watchOS = \"briefcase.platforms.watchOS\"\n177\t# wearos = \"briefcase.platforms.wearos\"\n178\tweb = \"briefcase.platforms.web\"\n179\twindows = \"briefcase.platforms.windows\"\n180\t\n181\t[project.entry-points.\"briefcase.formats.android\"]\n182\tgradle = \"briefcase.platforms.android.gradle\"\n183\t\n184\t[project.entry-points.\"briefcase.formats.iOS\"]\n185\tXcode = \"briefcase.platforms.iOS.xcode\"\n186\t\n187\t[project.entry-points.\"briefcase.formats.linux\"]\n188\tappimage = \"briefcase.platforms.linux.appimage\"\n189\tflatpak = \"briefcase.platforms.linux.flatpak\"\n190\tsystem = \"briefcase.platforms.linux.system\"\n191\t# snap = \"briefcase.platforms.linux.snap\"\n192\t\n193\t[project.entry-points.\"briefcase.formats.macOS\"]\n194\tapp = \"briefcase.platforms.macOS.app\"\n195\tXcode = \"briefcase.platforms.macOS.xcode\"\n196\t\n197\t# [project.entry-points.\"briefcase.formats.tvOS\"]\n198\t# Xcode = \"briefcase.platforms.tvOS.xcode\"\n199\t\n200\t# [project.entry-points.\"briefcase.formats.watchOS\"]\n201\t# Xcode = \"briefcase.platforms.watchOS.xcode\"\n202\t\n203\t# [project.entry-points.\"briefcase.formats.wearos\"]\n204\t# gradle = \"briefcase.platforms.wearos.gradle\"\n205\t\n206\t[project.entry-points.\"briefcase.formats.web\"]\n207\tstatic = \"briefcase.platforms.web.static\"\n208\t\n209\t[project.entry-points.\"briefcase.formats.windows\"]\n210\tapp = \"briefcase.platforms.windows.app\"\n211\tvisualstudio = \"briefcase.platforms.windows.visualstudio\"\n212\t\n213\t[project.entry-points.\"briefcase.channels.iOS.Xcode\"]\n214\tappstore = \"briefcase.channels.appstore:AppStorePublicationChannel\"\n215\t\n216\t[project.entry-points.\"briefcase.channels.android.gradle\"]\n217\tplaystore = \"briefcase.channels.playstore:PlayStorePublicationChannel\"\n218\t\n219\t[tool.coverage.run]\n220\tplugins = [\"coverage_conditional_plugin\"]\n221\tparallel = true\n222\tbranch = true\n223\trelative_files = true\n224\tsource_pkgs = [\"briefcase\"]\n225\t\n226\t[tool.coverage.paths]\n227\tsource = [\n228\t    \"src\",\n229\t    \"**/site-packages\",\n230\t]\n231\t\n232\t[tool.coverage.report]\n233\tshow_missing = true\n234\tskip_covered = true\n235\tskip_empty = true\n236\tprecision = 1\n237\texclude_lines = [\n238\t    \"pragma: no cover\",\n239\t    \"@(abc\\\\.)?abstractmethod\",\n240\t    \"@runtime_checkable\",\n241\t    \"NotImplementedError\\\\(\\\\)\",\n242\t    \"if TYPE_CHECKING:\",\n243\t]\n244\t\n245\t[tool.coverage.coverage_conditional_plugin.rules]\n246\tno-cover-if-missing-setuptools_scm = \"not is_installed('setuptools_scm')\"\n247\tno-cover-if-not-linux = \"'linux' != os_environ.get('COVERAGE_PLATFORM', sys_platform) and os_environ.get('COVERAGE_EXCLUDE_PLATFORM') != 'disable'\"\n248\tno-cover-if-is-macos = \"'darwin' == os_environ.get('COVERAGE_PLATFORM', sys_platform) and os_environ.get('COVERAGE_EXCLUDE_PLATFORM') != 'disable'\"\n249\tno-cover-if-not-macos = \"'darwin' != os_environ.get('COVERAGE_PLATFORM', sys_platform) and os_environ.get('COVERAGE_EXCLUDE_PLATFORM') != 'disable'\"\n250\tno-cover-if-is-windows = \"'win32' == os_environ.get('COVERAGE_PLATFORM', sys_platform) and os_environ.get('COVERAGE_EXCLUDE_PLATFORM') != 'disable'\"\n251\tno-cover-if-not-windows = \"'win32' != os_environ.get('COVERAGE_PLATFORM', sys_platform) and os_environ.get('COVERAGE_EXCLUDE_PLATFORM') != 'disable'\"\n252\tno-cover-if-gte-py312 = \"sys_version_info >= (3, 12) and os_environ.get('COVERAGE_EXCLUDE_PYTHON_VERSION') != 'disable'\"\n253\tno-cover-if-is-py312 = \"python_version == '3.12' and os_environ.get('COVERAGE_EXCLUDE_PYTHON_VERSION') != 'disable'\"\n254\tno-cover-if-lt-py312 = \"sys_version_info < (3, 12) and os_environ.get('COVERAGE_EXCLUDE_PYTHON_VERSION') != 'disable'\"\n255\tno-cover-if-lt-py311 = \"sys_version_info < (3, 11) and os_environ.get('COVERAGE_EXCLUDE_PYTHON_VERSION') != 'disable'\"\n256\tno-cover-if-gte-py311 = \"sys_version_info >= (3, 11) and os_environ.get('COVERAGE_EXCLUDE_PYTHON_VERSION') != 'disable'\"\n257\t\n258\t[tool.pytest.ini_options]\n259\ttestpaths = [\"tests\"]\n260\tfilterwarnings = [\n261\t    \"error\",\n262\t]\n263\t\n264\t# need to ensure build directories aren't excluded from recursion\n265\tnorecursedirs = []\n266\t\n267\t[tool.ruff.lint]\n268\t# In addition to the default rules, these additional rules will be used:\n269\textend-select = [\n270\t    \"E\",      # pycodestyle\n271\t    \"W\",      # pycodestyle\n272\t    \"F\",      # pyflakes\n273\t    \"UP\",     # pyupgrade\n274\t    \"B\",      # flake8-bugbear\n275\t    \"YTT\",    # flake8-2020\n276\t    \"ASYNC\",  # flake8-async\n277\t    \"C4\",     # flake8-comprehensions\n278\t    \"I\",      # isort\n279\t    \"RUF\",    # ruff-specific rules\n280\t    \"PT\",     # flake8-pytest-style\n281\t    \"FURB\",   # refurb\n282\t    \"ISC\",    # flake8-implicit-str-concat\n283\t    \"PGH\",    # pygrep-hooks\n284\t    \"T20\",    # flake8-print\n285\t    \"PIE\",    # flake8-pie\n286\t    \"SIM\",    # flake8-simplify\n287\t]\n288\t\n289\tignore = [\n290\t    \"SIM105\",  # use `contextlib.suppress` (too opinionated)\n291\t    \"SIM108\",  # replace if-else with ternary operator (too opinionated)\n292\t]\n293\t\n294\t[tool.ruff.lint.isort]\n295\t# If you've built a wheel locally, you'll have a build directory.\n296\t# This confuses ruff into thinking build is a first-party Python package.\n297\tknown-third-party = [\"build\"]\n298\t\n299\t[tool.ruff.lint.per-file-ignores]\n300\t# E501: line too long, to be fixed in future changes\n301\t\"tests/integrations/*\" = [\"E501\"]\n302\t\"tests/platforms/*\" = [\"E501\"]\n303\t\n304\t[tool.rumdl]\n305\tflavor = \"mkdocs\"\n306\tinclude = [\"**/*.md\"]\n307\texclude = [\"template.md\",]\n308\trespect-gitignore = true\n309\tforce-exclude = true\n310\t\n311\t# Disable rules:\n312\t# MD013: Line length - flagging on mkdocstrings content\n313\t# MD014: Forces commands in codeblocks to show output\n314\t# MD042: Empty link - buggy, still flagging on valid MkDocs formatting\n315\t# MD052: Reference link not found - buggy, flagging on valis MkDocs links\n316\tdisable = [\"MD014\", \"MD042\", \"MD052\"]\n317\t\n318\t[tool.rumdl.per-file-ignores]\n319\t\"changes/**/*.md\" = [\"MD041\"]\n320\t\n321\t[tool.rumdl.MD013]  # Line length\n322\tline_length = 999999  # Force reflow to paragraph content to remove linebreaks\n323\treflow = true\n324\treflow_mode = \"normalize\"\n325\t\n326\t[tool.rumdl.MD026]  # Remove punctuation at the end of headings\n327\tpunctuation = \",;:\"\n328\t\n329\t[tool.rumdl.MD033]  # No inline HTML\n330\tallowed_elements = [\"nospell\",]  # pyspelling inline disable tag\n331\t\n332\t[tool.rumdl.MD046]\n333\tstyle = \"fenced\"\n334\t\n335\t[tool.setuptools_scm]\n336\t# To enable SCM versioning, we need an empty tool configuration for setuptools_scm\n337\t\n338\t[tool.towncrier]\n339\tdirectory = \"changes\"\n340\tpackage = \"briefcase\"\n341\tpackage_dir = \"src\"\n342\tfilename = \"docs/en/about/releases.md\"\n343\ttitle_format = \"## {version} ({project_date})\"\n344\tissue_format = \"[#{issue}](https://github.com/beeware/briefcase/issues/{issue})\"\n345\ttemplate = \"changes/template.md\"\n346\ttype = [\n347\t    { directory = \"feature\", name = \"Features\", showcontent = true },\n348\t    { directory = \"bugfix\", name = \"Bugfixes\", showcontent = true },\n349\t    { directory = \"removal\", name = \"Backward Incompatible Changes\", showcontent = true },\n350\t    { directory = \"doc\", name = \"Documentation\", showcontent = true },\n351\t    { directory = \"misc\", name = \"Misc\", showcontent = false },\n352\t]\n353\t\n354\t[tool.ty.rules]\n355\tunresolved-attribute = \"warn\"\n356\tinvalid-argument-type = \"warn\"\n357\tinvalid-return-type = \"warn\"\n358\tunresolved-import = \"ignore\"\n359\t\n360\t[tool.codespell]\n361\tskip = '.git,*.pdf,*.svg'\n362\t# the way to make case-sensitive skips of words etc\n363\tignore-regex = '\\bNd\\b'\n364\t# case-insensitive\n365\t# ignore-words-list = ''\n366\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ea01d3a9-8bbc-42c9-956e-bd48a919071a","uuid":"f997a72c-432f-42a8-8616-e793181b64b5","timestamp":"2026-04-06T20:28:55.657Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/pyproject.toml","content":"[build-system]\nrequires = [\n    # keep versions in sync with automation/pyproject.toml\n    \"setuptools==82.0.1\",\n    \"setuptools_scm==10.0.5\",\n]\nbuild-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n\n[project]\ndynamic = [\"version\"]\nname = \"briefcase\"\ndescription = \"Tools to support converting a Python project into a standalone native application.\"\nreadme = \"README.md\"\nrequires-python = \">= 3.10\"\nlicense = \"BSD-3-Clause\"\nlicense-files = [\n    \"LICENSE\",\n]\nauthors = [\n    {name=\"Russell Keith-Magee\", email=\"russell@keith-magee.com\"},\n]\nmaintainers = [\n    {name=\"BeeWare Team\", email=\"team@beeware.org\"},\n]\nkeywords = [\n    \"app\",\n    \"packaging\",\n    \"installer\",\n    \"macOS\",\n    \"iOS\",\n    \"android\",\n    \"mobile\",\n    \"windows\",\n    \"linux\",\n    \"flatpak\",\n    \"appimage\",\n    \"deb\",\n    \"rpm\",\n    \"pkg\",\n    \"tvOS\",\n    \"watch\",\n    \"watchOS\",\n    \"wearos\",\n    \"web\",\n    \"pyscript\",\n    \"pyodide\",\n]\nclassifiers = [\n    \"Development Status :: 4 - Beta\",\n    \"Intended Audience :: Developers\",\n    \"Operating System :: OS Independent\",\n    \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3\",\n    \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10\",\n    \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11\",\n    \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12\",\n    \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13\",\n    \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.14\",\n    \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3 :: Only\",\n    \"Topic :: Software Development\",\n    \"Topic :: Utilities\",\n]\ndependencies = [\n    # Dependencies required at runtime are set as ranges to ensure maximum\n    # compatibility with the end-user's development environment.\n    #\n    # Any dependency that is part of the \"core python toolchain\" (e.g. pip, wheel)\n    # specify a minimum version, but no maximum, because we always want the most\n    # recent version.\n    \"packaging >= 24.2\",\n    \"pip >= 24.3\",\n    \"setuptools >= 60\",\n    \"wheel >= 0.37\",\n    \"build >= 0.10\",\n    \"truststore >= 0.10.1\",\n    #\n    # For the remaining packages: We set the lower version limit to the lowest possible\n    # version that satisfies our API needs. If the package uses semver, we set a limit\n    # to prevent the next major version (which will potentially cause API breakages).\n    # If the package uses calver, we don't pin the upper version, as the upper version\n    # provides no basis for determining API stability.\n    #\n    \"cookiecutter >= 2.6.0, < 3.0\",\n    # See psf/requests#7219. Requests 2.32.5 (a transitive dependency of cookiecutter)\n    # has a runtime warning about the use of chardet 6+, which our test suite turns into\n    # a full error. Requests has already increased the pin; the next requests release\n    # should remove the need for this pin.\n    \"chardet < 6.0\",\n    # See binaryornot/binaryornot#642 and binaryornot/binaryornot#649. binaryornot is\n    # transitive dependency of cookiecutter; v0.5.0 introduced #642, preventing correct\n    # detection of PNG content (#642). v0.6.0 (released a few days later) fixes #642,\n    # but introduced #649, and the presence of warnings causes catastrophic failures\n    # when running under dev mode.\n    \"binaryornot < 0.5.0\",\n    \"dmgbuild >= 1.6.4, < 2.0; sys_platform == 'darwin'\",\n    \"GitPython >= 3.1, < 4.0\",\n    \"platformdirs >= 2.6, < 5.0\",\n    \"psutil >= 5.9, < 8.0\",\n    \"python-dateutil >= 2.9.0.post0\",  # transitive dependency (beeware/briefcase#1428)\n    \"httpx >= 0.20, < 1.0\",\n    \"rich >= 12.6, < 15.0\",\n    \"tenacity >= 8.0, < 10.0\",\n    \"tomli >= 2.0, < 3.0; python_version <= '3.10'\",\n    \"tomli_w >= 1.0, < 2.0\",\n]\n\n[dependency-groups]\n# Extras used by developers *of* briefcase are pinned to specific versions to\n# ensure environment consistency.\npre-commit = [\n    \"pre-commit == 4.5.1\",\n]\n\nsetuptools-scm = [\n    \"setuptools_scm == 10.0.5\",\n]\n\ntowncrier = [\n    \"towncrier == 25.8.0\",\n]\n\ntox-uv = [\n    \"tox-uv == 1.34.0\",\n]\n\nty = [\n    \"ty == 0.0.29\",\n]\n\ndev = [\n    {include-group = \"pre-commit\"},\n    {include-group = \"setuptools-scm\"},\n    {include-group = \"tox-uv\"},\n]\n\ntest = [\n    \"coverage[toml] == 7.13.5\",\n    \"coverage-conditional-plugin == 0.9.0\",\n    \"httpx-retries == 0.4.6\",\n    \"pytest == 9.0.2\",\n    \"pytest-xdist == 3.8.0\",\n    {include-group = \"setuptools-scm\"},\n]\n# Docs are always built on a specific Python version; see RTD and tox config files,\n# and the docs contribution guide.\ndocs = [\n    \"beeware-docs-tools @ git+https://github.com/beeware/beeware-docs-tools\",\n]\n\n[project.urls]\nHomepage = \"https://beeware.org/briefcase\"\nFunding = \"https://beeware.org/contributing/membership/\"\nDocumentation = \"https://briefcase.readthedocs.io/en/latest/\"\nTracker = \"https://github.com/beeware/briefcase/issues\"\nSource = \"https://github.com/beeware/briefcase\"\n\n[project.scripts]\nbriefcase = \"briefcase.__main__:main\"\n\n[project.entry-points.\"briefcase.bootstraps\"]\nNone = \"briefcase.bootstraps.empty:EmptyBootstrap\"\nToga = \"briefcase.bootstraps.toga:TogaGuiBootstrap\"\nConsole = \"briefcase.bootstraps.console:ConsoleBootstrap\"\nPySide6 = \"briefcase.bootstraps.pyside6:PySide6GuiBootstrap\"\nPygame = \"briefcase.bootstraps.pygame:PygameGuiBootstrap\"\n\n[project.entry-points.\"briefcase.debuggers\"]\npdb = \"briefcase.debuggers.pdb:PdbDebugger\"\ndebugpy = \"briefcase.debuggers.debugpy:DebugpyDebugger\"\n\n[project.entry-points.\"briefcase.platforms\"]\nandroid = \"briefcase.platforms.android\"\niOS = \"briefcase.platforms.iOS\"\nlinux = \"briefcase.platforms.linux\"\nmacOS = \"briefcase.platforms.macOS\"\n# tvOS = \"briefcase.platforms.tvOS\"\n# watchOS = \"briefcase.platforms.watchOS\"\n# wearos = \"briefcase.platforms.wearos\"\nweb = \"briefcase.platforms.web\"\nwindows = \"briefcase.platforms.windows\"\n\n[project.entry-points.\"briefcase.formats.android\"]\ngradle = \"briefcase.platforms.android.gradle\"\n\n[project.entry-points.\"briefcase.formats.iOS\"]\nXcode = \"briefcase.platforms.iOS.xcode\"\n\n[project.entry-points.\"briefcase.formats.linux\"]\nappimage = \"briefcase.platforms.linux.appimage\"\nflatpak = \"briefcase.platforms.linux.flatpak\"\nsystem = \"briefcase.platforms.linux.system\"\n# snap = \"briefcase.platforms.linux.snap\"\n\n[project.entry-points.\"briefcase.formats.macOS\"]\napp = \"briefcase.platforms.macOS.app\"\nXcode = \"briefcase.platforms.macOS.xcode\"\n\n# [project.entry-points.\"briefcase.formats.tvOS\"]\n# Xcode = \"briefcase.platforms.tvOS.xcode\"\n\n# [project.entry-points.\"briefcase.formats.watchOS\"]\n# Xcode = \"briefcase.platforms.watchOS.xcode\"\n\n# [project.entry-points.\"briefcase.formats.wearos\"]\n# gradle = \"briefcase.platforms.wearos.gradle\"\n\n[project.entry-points.\"briefcase.formats.web\"]\nstatic = \"briefcase.platforms.web.static\"\n\n[project.entry-points.\"briefcase.formats.windows\"]\napp = \"briefcase.platforms.windows.app\"\nvisualstudio = \"briefcase.platforms.windows.visualstudio\"\n\n[project.entry-points.\"briefcase.channels.iOS.Xcode\"]\nappstore = \"briefcase.channels.appstore:AppStorePublicationChannel\"\n\n[project.entry-points.\"briefcase.channels.android.gradle\"]\nplaystore = \"briefcase.channels.playstore:PlayStorePublicationChannel\"\n\n[tool.coverage.run]\nplugins = [\"coverage_conditional_plugin\"]\nparallel = true\nbranch = true\nrelative_files = true\nsource_pkgs = [\"briefcase\"]\n\n[tool.coverage.paths]\nsource = [\n    \"src\",\n    \"**/site-packages\",\n]\n\n[tool.coverage.report]\nshow_missing = true\nskip_covered = true\nskip_empty = true\nprecision = 1\nexclude_lines = [\n    \"pragma: no cover\",\n    \"@(abc\\\\.)?abstractmethod\",\n    \"@runtime_checkable\",\n    \"NotImplementedError\\\\(\\\\)\",\n    \"if TYPE_CHECKING:\",\n]\n\n[tool.coverage.coverage_conditional_plugin.rules]\nno-cover-if-missing-setuptools_scm = \"not is_installed('setuptools_scm')\"\nno-cover-if-not-linux = \"'linux' != os_environ.get('COVERAGE_PLATFORM', sys_platform) and os_environ.get('COVERAGE_EXCLUDE_PLATFORM') != 'disable'\"\nno-cover-if-is-macos = \"'darwin' == os_environ.get('COVERAGE_PLATFORM', sys_platform) and os_environ.get('COVERAGE_EXCLUDE_PLATFORM') != 'disable'\"\nno-cover-if-not-macos = \"'darwin' != os_environ.get('COVERAGE_PLATFORM', sys_platform) and os_environ.get('COVERAGE_EXCLUDE_PLATFORM') != 'disable'\"\nno-cover-if-is-windows = \"'win32' == os_environ.get('COVERAGE_PLATFORM', sys_platform) and os_environ.get('COVERAGE_EXCLUDE_PLATFORM') != 'disable'\"\nno-cover-if-not-windows = \"'win32' != os_environ.get('COVERAGE_PLATFORM', sys_platform) and os_environ.get('COVERAGE_EXCLUDE_PLATFORM') != 'disable'\"\nno-cover-if-gte-py312 = \"sys_version_info >= (3, 12) and os_environ.get('COVERAGE_EXCLUDE_PYTHON_VERSION') != 'disable'\"\nno-cover-if-is-py312 = \"python_version == '3.12' and os_environ.get('COVERAGE_EXCLUDE_PYTHON_VERSION') != 'disable'\"\nno-cover-if-lt-py312 = \"sys_version_info < (3, 12) and os_environ.get('COVERAGE_EXCLUDE_PYTHON_VERSION') != 'disable'\"\nno-cover-if-lt-py311 = \"sys_version_info < (3, 11) and os_environ.get('COVERAGE_EXCLUDE_PYTHON_VERSION') != 'disable'\"\nno-cover-if-gte-py311 = \"sys_version_info >= (3, 11) and os_environ.get('COVERAGE_EXCLUDE_PYTHON_VERSION') != 'disable'\"\n\n[tool.pytest.ini_options]\ntestpaths = [\"tests\"]\nfilterwarnings = [\n    \"error\",\n]\n\n# need to ensure build directories aren't excluded from recursion\nnorecursedirs = []\n\n[tool.ruff.lint]\n# In addition to the default rules, these additional rules will be used:\nextend-select = [\n    \"E\",      # pycodestyle\n    \"W\",      # pycodestyle\n    \"F\",      # pyflakes\n    \"UP\",     # pyupgrade\n    \"B\",      # flake8-bugbear\n    \"YTT\",    # flake8-2020\n    \"ASYNC\",  # flake8-async\n    \"C4\",     # flake8-comprehensions\n    \"I\",      # isort\n    \"RUF\",    # ruff-specific rules\n    \"PT\",     # flake8-pytest-style\n    \"FURB\",   # refurb\n    \"ISC\",    # flake8-implicit-str-concat\n    \"PGH\",    # pygrep-hooks\n    \"T20\",    # flake8-print\n    \"PIE\",    # flake8-pie\n    \"SIM\",    # flake8-simplify\n]\n\nignore = [\n    \"SIM105\",  # use `contextlib.suppress` (too opinionated)\n    \"SIM108\",  # replace if-else with ternary operator (too opinionated)\n]\n\n[tool.ruff.lint.isort]\n# If you've built a wheel locally, you'll have a build directory.\n# This confuses ruff into thinking build is a first-party Python package.\nknown-third-party = [\"build\"]\n\n[tool.ruff.lint.per-file-ignores]\n# E501: line too long, to be fixed in future changes\n\"tests/integrations/*\" = [\"E501\"]\n\"tests/platforms/*\" = [\"E501\"]\n\n[tool.rumdl]\nflavor = \"mkdocs\"\ninclude = [\"**/*.md\"]\nexclude = [\"template.md\",]\nrespect-gitignore = true\nforce-exclude = true\n\n# Disable rules:\n# MD013: Line length - flagging on mkdocstrings content\n# MD014: Forces commands in codeblocks to show output\n# MD042: Empty link - buggy, still flagging on valid MkDocs formatting\n# MD052: Reference link not found - buggy, flagging on valis MkDocs links\ndisable = [\"MD014\", \"MD042\", \"MD052\"]\n\n[tool.rumdl.per-file-ignores]\n\"changes/**/*.md\" = [\"MD041\"]\n\n[tool.rumdl.MD013]  # Line length\nline_length = 999999  # Force reflow to paragraph content to remove linebreaks\nreflow = true\nreflow_mode = \"normalize\"\n\n[tool.rumdl.MD026]  # Remove punctuation at the end of headings\npunctuation = \",;:\"\n\n[tool.rumdl.MD033]  # No inline HTML\nallowed_elements = [\"nospell\",]  # pyspelling inline disable tag\n\n[tool.rumdl.MD046]\nstyle = \"fenced\"\n\n[tool.setuptools_scm]\n# To enable SCM versioning, we need an empty tool configuration for setuptools_scm\n\n[tool.towncrier]\ndirectory = \"changes\"\npackage = \"briefcase\"\npackage_dir = \"src\"\nfilename = \"docs/en/about/releases.md\"\ntitle_format = \"## {version} ({project_date})\"\nissue_format = \"[#{issue}](https://github.com/beeware/briefcase/issues/{issue})\"\ntemplate = \"changes/template.md\"\ntype = [\n    { directory = \"feature\", name = \"Features\", showcontent = true },\n    { directory = \"bugfix\", name = \"Bugfixes\", showcontent = true },\n    { directory = \"removal\", name = \"Backward Incompatible Changes\", showcontent = true },\n    { directory = \"doc\", name = \"Documentation\", showcontent = true },\n    { directory = \"misc\", name = \"Misc\", showcontent = false },\n]\n\n[tool.ty.rules]\nunresolved-attribute = \"warn\"\ninvalid-argument-type = \"warn\"\ninvalid-return-type = \"warn\"\nunresolved-import = \"ignore\"\n\n[tool.codespell]\nskip = '.git,*.pdf,*.svg'\n# the way to make case-sensitive skips of words etc\nignore-regex = '\\bNd\\b'\n# case-insensitive\n# ignore-words-list = ''\n","numLines":366,"startLine":1,"totalLines":366}}}
